This file only keeps repository-wide guidance. Put app-specific and workflow-specific rules in path-scoped rule files to avoid duplication.

## Repository Layout

- `src/AiChatCLI/` contains the .NET 9 console app.
- `tests/AiChatCLI.Tests/` contains focused xUnit tests for app seams such as path resolution, slash-command output, and thread replay/message mapping.
- `devtools/workflow/` contains the Python workflow runner for Cursor CLI.
- `devtools/cli-session/` contains the Python session wrapper for interactive CLI processes.
- Read the nearest README before making substantive changes:
  - `README.md`
  - `src/AiChatCLI/README.md`
  - `devtools/workflow/README.md`
  - `devtools/cli-session/README.md`
- Keep user-facing behavior documented in the nearest README as part of the same change.
- When project conventions or architecture guidance change, update the matching `.cursor/rules/` file in the same task.

## Common Commands

```bash
dotnet build
dotnet test AiChatCLI.sln
dotnet run --project src/AiChatCLI/AiChatCLI.csproj
```

No shared lint command is configured at the repository root.
